      <title>Use Dioptas for Efficient 2D Powder Diffraction Data Reduction</title>
      <link href="/Tools/Use%20Dioptas%20for%20Efficient%202D%20Powder%20Diffraction%20Data%20Reduction.html"/>
      <url>/Tools/Use%20Dioptas%20for%20Efficient%202D%20Powder%20Diffraction%20Data%20Reduction.html</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<link rel="stylesheet" type="text&#x2F;css" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/hexo-tag-hint@0.3.1/dist/hexo-tag-hint.min.css"><img src="https://oss.huaecho.cn/blogimage/Dioptas/cover.png?imageMogr2/formatavif" alt="2D Powder Diffraction" title="2D Powder Diffraction" width="50%"><p>Dioptas is an awesome GUI program based on <em>Python</em>, designed for the fast data reduction of <em><strong>Powder X-ray Diffraction images</strong></em>. It provides the capability of <strong>calibrating</strong>, <strong>integrating</strong>, <strong>creating masks</strong>, showing multiple pattern overlays and display phases line positions.</p><span id="more"></span><img src="https://oss.huaecho.cn/blogimage/Dioptas/Dioptas_Modules.png?imageMogr2/formatavif" alt="Dioptas_Modules" title="Dioptas_Modules" width="60%"><h2 id="Program-dependencies">Program dependencies</h2><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tbody><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">Python 3.9+</span><br><span class="line">pyFAI</span><br></pre></td></tr></tbody></table></figure><h2 id="Distribution">Distribution</h2><p><strong>Maintainer</strong></p><p>Clemens Prescher (<a href="mailto:clemens.prescher@gmail.com">clemens.prescher@gmail.com</a>)</p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tbody><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">https://github.com/Dioptas/Dioptas</span><br></pre></td></tr></tbody></table></figure><h2 id="Installation">Installation</h2><p><strong>Executables</strong></p><p>Binary programs for Windows, macOS, and Linux can be downloaded from the following link:</p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tbody><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">https://github.com/Dioptas/Dioptas/releases</span><br></pre></td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p><strong>pip</strong></p><p>Install the all the dependencies for <em>Dioptas</em> by pip package manager:</p><figure class="highlight shell"><table><tbody><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">pip install dioptas</span><br><span class="line"><span class="meta prompt_"># </span><span class="language-bash">run Dioptas</span></span><br><span class="line">dioptas</span><br></pre></td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p><strong>poetry</strong><br>Use the poetry package manager to create a working environment by typing:</p><figure class="highlight shell"><table><tbody><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="meta prompt_"># </span><span class="language-bash">create new environment</span></span><br><span class="line">poetry install</span><br><span class="line"><span class="meta prompt_"># </span><span class="language-bash">Activate the environment</span></span><br><span class="line">poetry shell</span><br><span class="line"><span class="meta prompt_"># </span><span class="language-bash">run dioptas</span></span><br><span class="line">dioptas</span><br><span class="line"><span class="meta prompt_"># </span><span class="language-bash">run the dioptas without activating the environment</span></span><br><span class="line">poetry run dioptas</span><br></pre></td></tr></tbody></table></figure><h2 id="Procedure">Procedure</h2><h3 id="Workflow">Workflow</h3><pre class="mermaid">flowchart LR    A(Load Image Data) --&gt;B(Calibration)    B --&gt; C(Marks)    C --&gt; D(Integration)    D --&gt; E(Export Data)    D --&gt;A</pre><h3 id="Overview">Overview</h3><p>Dioptas has three different modules which can all be accessed by the lab indicators on the <em><strong>left side</strong></em> of the user interface: <strong>Calibration</strong>, <strong>Mask</strong>, <strong>Integration</strong>.</p><ul><li><strong>Calibration Module</strong> This module is used to calibrate the detector geometry.</li><li><strong>Mask Module</strong> This module allows users to select regions that need to be excluded from the image integration.</li><li><strong>Integration Module</strong> This module displays the image and integrated pattern. It can overlay different patterns and show the line positions of phases.</li></ul><hr><h3 id="Getting-Started">Getting Started</h3><p>Basic Mouse Operations</p><ul><li><strong>Left Drag</strong> Zooms into the selected area.</li></ul><img src="https://oss.huaecho.cn/blogimage/Dioptas/leftclick.gif?imageMogr2/formatavif" alt="Left Drag" title="Left Drag" width="60%"><ul><li><strong>Right Click</strong> Zoom out.</li></ul><img src="https://oss.huaecho.cn/blogimage/Dioptas/rightclick.gif?imageMogr2/formatavif" alt="Right Click" title="Right Click" width="60%"><ul><li><strong>Right Double Click</strong> Completely Zoom out.</li></ul><img src="https://oss.huaecho.cn/blogimage/Dioptas/rightdclick.gif?imageMogr2/formatavif" alt="Right Double Click" title="Right Double Click" width="60%"><ul><li><strong>Mouse Wheel</strong> Zoom in and zoom out based on the current cursor position.</li></ul><img src="https://oss.huaecho.cn/blogimage/Dioptas/mousewheel.gif?imageMogr2/formatavif" alt="Mouse Wheel" title="Mouse Wheel" width="60%"><p>Image Color Scale and Contrast<br>The image color scale and contrast can be adjusted by sliding the color bar and right-clicking to change the color group.</p><img src="https://oss.huaecho.cn/blogimage/Dioptas/colorscal.gif?imageMogr2/formatavif" alt="Color Scale and Constrast" title="Color Scale and Constrast" width="60%"><p>Let's start by loading the image data.<br>Clicking <button type="button"><strong>Load file</strong></button> button the on the upper right side of the interface to</p><h3 id="Calibration-Procedure">Calibration Procedure</h3><p>The callibration procedure aim to correct the detector geometry.</p><h4 id="Preparation">Preparation</h4><p>First, click the <button type="button"><strong>Calibration</strong></button> button to enter calibration mode.<br>The <em>wavelength</em> and <em>pixel width/height</em> <strong>have to</strong> be defined based on the experimental setup and detector used.</p><img src="https://oss.huaecho.cn/blogimage/Dioptas/calpara.png?imageMogr2/formatavif" alt="Calibration Parameter" title="Calibration Parameter" width="60%"><p>Required Parameter Setting:</p><ul><li>Calibrant (standard complex)</li><li>wavelength</li><li>pixel width</li><li>pixel height</li><li>Distance (the program will automatically refine the value)</li></ul><h4 id="Peak-Picking">Peak Picking</h4><h4 id="Calibration">Calibration</h4><h3 id="Mask-Creation">Mask Creation</h3><h3 id="Integration-Procedure">Integration Procedure</h3><h3 id="Exporting-Data">Exporting Data</h3><h3 id="References">References</h3><blockquote><p>[1] <a href="https://doi.org/10.1080/08957959.2015.1059835">Prescher, Clemens, and Vitali B. Prakapenka. “DIOPTAS: A Program for Reduction of Two-Dimensional X-Ray Diffraction Data and Data Exploration.” High Pressure Research 35, no. 3 (2015): 223–30. doi:10.1080/08957959.2015.1059835.</a><br>[2] <a href="https://dioptas.readthedocs.io/en/stable/index.html">Dioptas 0.4.0 documentation</a><br>[3] <a href="https://github.com/Dioptas/Dioptas">github.com/Dioptas/Dioptas.git</a></p></blockquote><script type="text&#x2F;javascript" src="https://unpkg.com/kity@2.0.4/dist/kity.min.js"></script><script type="text&#x2F;javascript" src="https://unpkg.com/kityminder-core@1.4.50/dist/kityminder.core.min.js"></script><script defer="true" type="text&#x2F;javascript" src="https://unpkg.com/hexo-simple-mindmap@0.8.0/dist/mindmap.min.js"></script><link rel="stylesheet" type="text&#x2F;css" href="https://unpkg.com/hexo-simple-mindmap@0.8.0/dist/mindmap.min.css">]]></content>
      
      
